						               													<description>The third game in the Scarlet Envelope series.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If you love detectives and sci-fi, this tabletop escape room by Scarlet Envelope is for you. The year is 2220, a century into human colonization of Mars. Your spaceship picks up the distress call from a Martian spy who has discovered a dark secret that can stop the war between Earth and Mars! Now, encrypted Martian files are in your hands, along with the fate of our Galaxy. Will you accept the challenge?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;GAME CONTENTS:&amp;#10;- A huge space map (you&amp;rsquo;ll be surprised that it fits into the envelope!)&amp;#10;- Constellations map&amp;#10;- A cryptic ruler (to be used together with a map)&amp;#10;- Piece of evidence on a transparent film&amp;#10;- Audio SOS-signal from the Martian spy&amp;#10;- Spaceship Main Control interactive terminal (use commands to access info &amp;amp; additional files)&amp;#10;- &amp;ldquo;Earth Today&amp;rdquo; web news portal&amp;#10;- Two more hidden websites&amp;#10;- Two more hidden digital files&amp;#10;- Email correspondence with the United Planets Secretary-General&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A fun detective investigation narrative with over a dozen of various puzzles to solve, from encryption to altering items. You will need a computer or a mobile device to play. Expect a lot of digital interaction (it&amp;rsquo;s the 23rd century after all.) Answer submission and a storytelling video at the end. Tons of quality time in the middle!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;-description from publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
